title: Looking back and ahead at Utah's football schedule following bye week
text:
Sept. 3 — MICHIGAN, won 24-17 
Sept. 11 — UTAH STATE, won 24-14 
Sept. 19 — at Fresno State, won 45-24 
Sept. 26 — at Oregon, won 62-20 
Oct. 10 — CALIFORNIA, 8 p.m. (ESPN) 
Oct. 17 — ARIZONA STATE, TBA 
Oct. 24 — at USC, TBA 
Oct. 31 — OREGON STATE, TBA 
Nov. 7 — at Washington, TBA 
Nov. 14 — at Arizona, TBA 
Nov. 21 — UCLA, TBA 
Nov. 28 — COLORADO, TBA 
All times Mountain 
Utah had its first bye of the season this week but still jumped to No. 5 in the Associated Press poll and No. 7 in the Amway Coaches Poll. The Utes return to action Saturday at Rice-Eccles Stadium against the Cal Bears. Here's a look of how each team on Utah's schedule performed over the weekend: 
MICHIGAN (4-1): Defeated Maryland, 28-0 . Up next: Saturday vs. Northwestern (5-0). 
UTAH STATE (2-2): Defeated Colorado State, 33-18 . Up next: Saturday at Fresno State (1-4). 
FRESNO STATE (1-4): Lost at San Diego State, 21-7 . Up next: Saturday vs. Utah State (2-2). 
OREGON (3-2, 1-1): Defeated Colorado, 41-24 . Up next: Saturday vs. Washington State (2-2, 0-1). 
CALIFORNIA (5-0, 2-0): Defeated Washington State, 34-28 . Up next: Saturday at Utah (4-0, 1-0). 
ARIZONA STATE (3-2, 1-1): Defeated UCLA, 38-23 . Up next: Saturday vs. Colorado (3-2, 0-1). 
USC (3-1, 1-1): Had a bye. Up next: Thursday vs. Washington (2-2, 0-1). 
OREGON STATE (2-2, 0-1): Had a bye. Up next: Saturday at Arizona (3-2, 0-2). 
WASHINGTON (2-2, 0-1): Had a bye. Up next: Thursday at USC (3-1, 1-1). 
ARIZONA (3-2, 0-2): Lost at Stanford, 55-17 . Up next: Saturday vs. Oregon State (2-2, 0-1). 
UCLA (4-1, 1-1): Lost to Arizona State, 38-23 . Up next: Oct. 15 at Stanford (4-1, 3-0). 
COLORADO (3-2, 0-1): Lost to Oregon, 41-24 . Up next: Saturday at Arizona State (3-2, 1-1). Related Stories
